<p>The <code>capitalize</code> function capitalizes the first letter of each word.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'hello world' | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{'hello world' | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>From Lowercase</h2>
<pre>{open}'JOHN DOE' | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Fixed caps: <b>{'JOHN DOE' | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}$sampleEmail | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Full name from email: <b>{$sampleEmail | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'the quick brown fox' | capitalize | left(13){close}...</pre>
<p>Title preview: <b>{'the quick brown fox' | capitalize | left(13)}...</b></p>

<h2>With Users</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  {open}$email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>
<p>Names from emails:</p>
{users}
  {$email | before('@') | replace('.', ' ') | capitalize}<br>
{/users}

<h2>Complex Chain</h2>
<pre>{open}'product_category_name' | replace('_', ' ') | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>From snake_case: <b>{'product_category_name' | replace('_', ' ') | capitalize}</b></p>
